name: Albany Park River Restoration Self-guided Tour
description: Self-guided tour around a recently completed river restoration and wetlands project in Albany Park
address: Albany Park, Albany Road, Enfield, EN3 5PA

name: Aldgate Square
description: Publicly accessible landscaped Square featuring a pavilion with an asymmetrical steel structure and sliding glass walls set between three triangular support points. Also a stunning contemporary outdoor artwork from Sculpture in the City.

name: BCA Barnes Trail - self-guided walk
description: This is a self-guided 2.3 mile circular trail - with a 3 mile extension - and has been designed to show Barnes at its best - just follow the silver 'Barnes Trail' discs in the ground. The oar signs en route tell you what to look for.

name: Barons Court and West Kensington self guided walk
description: This walk compiled by Fulham Society experts covers an area developed around the turn of the nineteenth/twentieth centuries and colonised for an eclectic mix of artistic people, commercial uses and a little known cemetery.

name: Brasted Close
description: This project for 11 homes is the result of a campaign by local people to build affordable homes on surplus council-owned land, and will be among the first CLT homes completed in London. Shortlisted for the Open City Stewardship Awards 2021.

name: C20 x Open House Festival Self-Guided tour – Buildings at Risk
description: As an introduction to our work, we invite you to visit some of our recent Buildings at Risk. This is a small selection of examples in London, that can be visited from the outside and that are walking distance from each other.

name: Covent Garden Market
description: This iconic London destination has been managed for the past 15 years by Capital and Counties with a hands-on approach, and operational support from Incentive FM. Shortlisted for the Open City Stewardship Awards 2021.

name: Guildhall Yard
description: Publicly accessible space outside the spectacular Grade I listed medieval civic Guildhall. Located above the remains of London's Roman amphitheatre, the outline of the arena is marked out by black paving stones within the Yard itself.

name: Liverpool Everyman Theatre
description: A Stirling Prize-winning project from masters of theatre design, Haworth Tompkins, which is now a key example in their internal post-occupancy led learning, developing future practice. Shortlisted for the Open City Stewardship Awards 2021.

name: Luxmore Gardens
description: Self-guided walk. Enter Luxmore Gardens via Luxmore St (off Malpas Rd) or one of the two alleyways on Rokeby Rd. Stroll through the park and link up with the Brockley Mews walks or walk to Hilly Fields to begin the 3 Peaks Circular walk.

name: Meridian Water Art - Self Guided Tour
description: A self-guided walking tour of three new artworks on hoarding surrounding the first phase of the £6 billion Meridian Water project. This self-guided tour compliments a separate walking tour with artist Adam David.
address: Meridian Waters Train Station, Enfield, N18 3AH

name: Neighbourhood Walks and Heritage Walks
description: Explore Croydon and learn about your local area with illustrated walks that you can print at home. Accessed here: http://www.croydon.gov.uk/walks

name: Richmond: heart, hearth and hill
description: A story about a place that lies at the heart of the town; a visit to a lost palace from which Richmond’s name came to be; a bridge that connects the two halves and a steady, awe-inspiring climb that will present a view like no other.

name: Self-guided Evidences of the Black Presence in Hackney
description: A number of places testify to the Black Presence in Hackney. These are at some distance from each other. Visiting them would require time and transport but there are frequent bus services.

name: Self-guided Hanger Hill (Haymills) Estate Walk
description: Rare amongst 1930s London suburbs for a large number of modern movement residences in buildings designed by a single practice (Welch, Lander & Cachemaille-Day) as a series of concentric crescents.

name: Self-guided Hanger Hill Garden Estate Walk
description: Designated a conservation area in 1969 – one of the first in Britain. Built between 1928 and 1936 the Estate houses and flats are all in the Tudor half-timbered style of architecture within a formal landscape setting.

name: Self-guided Modern Architecture Walk – East Putney
description:
Highlights from Putney Society's Modern Architecture Gazetteer in a self-guided walk in East Putney.
Download or print   https://www.putneysociety.org.uk/putney_society_files/Buildings-Panel/Modern_Architecture_Walk_1_Putney_East.pdf

name: Self-guided Modern Architecture Walk – Putney Heath
description:
Highlights from the Putney Society's Modern Architecture Gazetteer in a self-guided walk around Putney Heath.
Start Portsmouth Road and finish Green Man PH.
address: Far end (western) of Portsmouth Road, Putney Heath, SW15 3TJ

name: Self-guided River Lee Navigation Walk
description: The Hackney stretch of the historic Lee Valley Navigation is particularly accessible, busy and interesting. Choc-a-bloc with canal moorings, it exemplifies an alternative way of living.
address: Clapton Station, Upper Clapton Road, E5 9JP

name: The High Cross
description: Former public conveniences with an array of internal and external original features

name: Trent Park
description: A truly exquisite Grade II country mansion designed in the early Georgian style, nestling in a 413-acre estate of stunning open parklands, woods, and historic landscaped gardens has been meticulously refurbished by Berkeley.
address: Trent Park, Snakes Lane, Cockfosters, EN4 0PS

name: UCL - The Bartlett School of Architecture
description: This refurbishment and extension to University College London’s 22 Gordon Street provides an environmentally responsible home for the prestigious Bartlett School of Architecture. Shortlisted for the Open City Stewardship Awards 2021.
